A beautifully simple and tasty chicken dish - quicker and healthier than any
Share to Facebook Share to Twitter Email Print
1. Spray potatoes with a little olive oil and roast in oven whilst you prep and cook the chicken.
2. Spray or brush a small ovenproof dish with a little oil. Place chicken fillets in a single layer.
3. In a small bowl, mix honey, mustard and garlic together. Spread over chicken. Cover the dish with baking paper or aluminium foil.
4. Bake chicken at 180°C (350°F) for 5 minutes. Uncover, baste with the juices, and cook for a further 5 minutes or so until tender.
5. Serve with steamed or microwaved broccolini or green beans and baked baby potatoes.
This recipe requires very little time and effort for how good it tastes. The
perfect meal to practice healthier portions: 1/4 plate lean meat (chicken) +
1/4 plate high fibre carbohydrates (chat potatoes) + 1/2 plate non-starchy
